ooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    44→    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    45→    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n    46→  }\\n    47→}\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→Note: The file is a Kiro agent definition. Hooks must be nested under the `hooks` field.\\n    51→Required top-level fields: `name`. Optional: `$schema`, `description`, `prompt`, `mcpServers`,\\n    52→`tools`, `toolAliases`, `allowedTools`, `resources`, `hooks`, `toolsSettings`, `model`, etc.\\n    53→\\n    54→**Important:** The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools. Without it, `--agent entire`\\n    55→restricts the model to zero tools. The tool names come from `~/.kiro/agents/agent_config.json.example`.\\n    56→\\n    57→## Agent Activation\\n    58→\\n    59→Hooks only fire when `--agent entire` is passed to `kiro-cli chat`. Without this flag,\\n    60→`.kiro/agents/entire.json` is not loaded and hooks do not execute.\\n    61→\\n    62→**`--no-interactive` mode:** Does not fire agent hooks. All E2E tests use interactive (tmux) mode.\\n    63→\\n    64→**TUI prompt indicator:** `!>` in trust-all mode (with `-a` flag). The `Credits:` line\\n    65→appears after each agent response and serves as a reliable completion marker.\\n    66→\\n    67→## Hook Stdin Format\\n    68→\\n    69→All hooks receive the same JSON structure on stdin:\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\n    72→  \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\",\\n    73→  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n    74→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user message\\\",\\n    75→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\",\\n    76→  \\\"tool_input\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    77→  \\\"tool_response\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→Fields are populated based on the hook event — `prompt` only for `userPromptSubmit`, tool fields only for tool hooks.\\n    82→\\n    83→## Transcript Storage\\n    84→\\n    85→**Source:** SQLite databa