un test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThe E2E runner should compile with the new `unsetEnv` parameter. Behavior is only observable during actual E2E runs.\",\"new_string\":\"# Fix Kiro E2E Authentication in CI\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nKiro E2E tests fail in CI because `kiro-cli` is not authenticated. Unlike other agents (Claude Code, Gemini, Droid) that use simple API keys, Kiro uses Amazon Q Builder ID OAuth. In CI, kiro-cli shows the browser sign-in prompt and the tests time out waiting for the `!>` prompt.\\n\\n**Auth token location:** `~/.aws/sso/cache/kiro-auth-token.json`\\n**Token structure:** `{ accessToken, refreshToken, profileArn, expiresAt, authMethod, provider }`\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Update `Bootstrap()` to write auth token — `e2e/agents/kiro.go`\\n\\nFollow the same pattern as Claude Code (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` → `~/.claude/.claude.json`) and Droid (`FACTORY_API_KEY` → `~/.factory/settings.json`).\\n\\n**New `Bootstrap()` logic:**\\n1. If not in CI (`os.Getenv(\\\"CI\\\") == \\\"\\\"`), return nil (local auth via desktop app)\\n2. Read `KIRO_AUTH_TOKEN` env var — if empty, return nil (agent skipped gracefully)\\n3. Create `~/.aws/sso/cache/` directory (`os.MkdirAll`)\\n4. Write the token JSON to `~/.aws/sso/cache/kiro-auth-token.json` with `0o600` permissions (sensitive)\\n5. Keep the existing `kiro-cli whoami` verification check after writing the token\\n\\n**Pattern reference:** Claude bootstrap at `e2e/agents/claude.go:90-111`\\n\\n### 2. Add `KIRO_AUTH_TOKEN` to CI workflow — `.github/workflows/e2e.yml`\\n\\nAdd `KIRO_AUTH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.KIRO_AUTH_TOKEN }}` to both the \\\"Bootstrap agent\\\" and \\\"Run E2E Tests\\\" steps' `env` blocks (lines 45-48 and 51-56).\\n\\n**The secret value** should be the full JSON content of `~/.aws/sso/cache/kiro-auth-token.json` (obtained via `kiro-cli login --use-device-flow` on a remote/CI machine).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nFull validation requires the `